results.snippet: By one of the most common of the Washington criteria for success, namely ability to secure money, the National Aeronautics and Space Administration must rank as one of the most successful Federal agencies of all time. In less than 11 years of...
results.lead_paragraph: By one of the most common of the Washington criteria for success, namely ability to secure money, the National Aeronautics and Space Administration must rank as one of the most successful Federal agencies of all time. In less than 11 years of existence NASA has obtained and spent almost $35-billion. For an agency that is predominantly civilian, this is truly remarkable.
